discusses nanoscale field-effect transistors and alternative device concepts such as Schottky-barrier MOSFETs as well as steep slope transistors based on different materials. In addition, cryogenic operation of MOSFETs for the realization of, e.g., classical control electronics of semiconducting spin qubits is studied. The work contains a number of tasks, examples and exercises with step-by-step video solutions as well as tutorial videos that deepen the understanding of the material. With additional access to simulation tools that allow students to do computational experiments, the emphasis is on thorough explanation of the material enabling students to carry out their own research.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aNanoelectronics. 4aElektronischer Transport. 4aFeldeffekt-Transistoren. 4aHalbleiterfertigung. 4aMetalloxid-Halbleiter. 4aZweidimensionale Materialien. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Condensed Matter.2bisacsh  aElectronic Transport.  aField-Effect Transistors.  aMetal-Oxide Semiconductor.  aSemiconductor Fabrication.  aTwo-Dimensional Materials.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z97831113321920 cEPUBz97831110550150 cprintz978311105424740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311105442140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111054421423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111054421/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles